Duff and Phelps said it lowered theratings on Duquesne Light Company fixed income securities,affecting approximately 1.8 billion dlrs in debt.    Duquesne first mortgage bonds and debentures were loweredto DP-9 (middle BBB) from DP-8 (high BBB), preferred stockrating to DP-10 (low BBB) from DP-9 and preference stock toDP-11 (high BB) from DP-10.    The change resulted from a denial by the PennsylvaniaPublic Utility Commission for a rate increase and an order bythe commission to reduce rates by 18.6 mln dlrs annually. Reuter&#3;